snippet.textDisplay: People in the U.S. shouldn't get too hyperactive over the Wuhan Coronavirus. The news headlines are designed to provoke panic and/or outrage to keep people checking in for updates and giving more views. It's essentially just a stronger cold. Over 19 million people have been infected with the influenza virus this flu season alone. That is something to be a lot more concerned about because the flu kills a lot more people. But the flu isn't "new and exciting" so that's why the attention is directed towards a new virus (that is way more mild compared to the flu).
